<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, "I guess fame is relative," comments author Philip Varney dryly as he 
observes the sign advertising "Famous ABC Beer" on the side of this abandoned 
commercial building in the town of Keeler. Varney identifies Keeler, located 16 
miles outside of Lone Pine on state route 136, as one of "Southern California's 
Best Ghost Towns" (see review this page), and notes that the town's most 
prominent structure, the Sierra Talc Co., has been "a favorite subject of 
artists." No doubt that distinction, too, is relative. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
