<HEADLINE>
<P>
CENSUS NEARLY MISSES ST. PAUL'S MAYOR SCHEIBEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. PAUL, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One citizen whom the U.S. Census Bureau almost missed this year was Mayor Jim 
Scheibel -- but officials promised to right their mistake. 
</P>
<P>
Scheibel's apartment was among the 5,000 households in the St. Paul area that 
did not receive census forms. 
</P>
<P>
"I'd been promoting the census and the importance of filling out the forms when 
I realized I didn't have a form," Scheibel said last week. "They almost didn't 
count the mayor." 
</P>
<P>
Rod Swenson, district manager of the St. Paul census office, called Scheibel to 
assure him that a form was on the way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
