<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SPRING VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 12-year-old boy was struck by a car Friday in Spring Valley and taken to 
Children's Hospital, where he was listed in fair condition Saturday, a hospital 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
James Rainbolt, a Spring Valley resident, suffered head injuries after he was 
hit, said spokeswoman Jeannie Berghorn. The boy was transported by Life Flight 
helicopter to the hospital at 6:36 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Officials have not yet released details on the cause of the incident. 
</P>
