<LENGTH>
<P>
63 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTLEHEIM'S DEATH: SOCIETY'S DISGRACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Patt Morrison's illuminating article, "Last Days of Bruno Bettleheim" (April 
3), was a courageous and unflinching look at what can happen to the unloved 
elderly. 
</P>
<P>
That such a gentle and caring man as Bettleheim could end his life so brutally 
uncared for is a disgrace. Unfortunately, in our society this particular 
disgrace is a common one. 
</P>
<P>
GLORIA KAUFMAN 
</P>
<P>
West Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
