<P>
Opinion; Part M; Page 6; Column 4; Letters Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
92 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEMOCRATIC PRIMARY RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For 10 years I have watched in frustration as the Republicans (for the most 
part) smeared the Democrats with negative campaign advertisements. 
</P>
<P>
Now it appears that the Democrats are going to employ the same disgusting 
tactics on each other. How delightful it is to face another election in which 
none of the candidates are worthy of my vote. 
</P>
<P>
One would hope that citizens of good conscience would refrain from voting for a 
candidate who employs such ads. Unfortunately, the wicked are usually elected 
anyway. 
</P>
<P>
PAUL E. STEVENSON 
</P>
<P>
Playa del Rey 
</P>
