<P>
HARRY BRIDGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The death of Harry Bridges (Part A, March 31) marks the passing of a remarkable 
American citizen of Marxist persuasion, whose honesty and dedication place him 
among the highest level in the history of the American labor movement. 
</P>
<P>
He lived modestly and did not enrich himself at the expense of his workers. 
Instead he consistently fought for their rights and interests. 
</P>
<P>
Bridges will be remembered for many years to come, while many of his detractors 
are among the forgotten. 
</P>
<P>
