<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUDENT HIT BY CAR AS PALM SPRINGS BRACES FOR FINAL ONSLAUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PALMS SPRINGS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A young man was struck and injured by a car Saturday as authorities braced for 
the final onslaught of party-minded spring break vacationers who annually 
converge on this desert community. 
</P>
<P>
The accident was the latest serious incident involving high school and college 
students who flock to the Southern California desert as part of the annual rite 
of spring. 
</P>
<P>
Last week, a teen-age girl died and three others were injured when a 
drag-racing car crossed the center line of a Rancho Mirage highway and crashed 
head-on with a small sports car. 
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's incident, the victim, described by police as in his late teens or 
early 20s, was hit by a car in the 400 block of East Palm Canyon Drive outside 
a district heavily dotted with hotels. Further information on the accident and 
the victim was unavailable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
