<P>
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Foreign Aid Amendment 
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 72 to 346, the House rejected an amendment to HR 4404 (above) 
shaving about $33 million from the bill's aid to Panama, Israel and Nicaragua. 
Sponsor James A. Traficant Jr.(D-Ohio) said: "I'm tired of foreign aid" at the 
expense of domestic needs. Opponent Mickey Edwards (R-Okla.) said the amendment 
would not lower spending but leave the money in the defense budget. 
</P>
<P>
Members voting yes supported the amendment. 
</P>
