<HEADLINE>
<P>
25 BODIES DISCOVERED IN COMMON COLOMBIA GRAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOGOTA, Colombia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The bodies of 25 people, some of whom had been missing for months, were found 
buried in a common grave in northern Colombia, Gen. Octavio Vargas, chief of 
police operations, said. 
</P>
<P>
Vargas said the bodies were found Wednesday near the town of Valencia on the 
property of Fidel Castano. 
</P>
